  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bb1\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbe\u0bb0 \u0ba8\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bbf \u0bae\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcb\u0b9a\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0bae\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0ba4 \u0b89\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0bae\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bc0\u0bb1\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bcb\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0baa\u0baf \u0baa\u0bca\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc2\u0bb1 \u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd - \u0b89\u0bb2\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bb5\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Gotabaya must be held accountable not only for economic mismanagement but also for gross human rights abuses - World Tamil Council",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "The World Tamil Council has congratulated the great political victory achieved by the united people in Sri Lanka, and has expressed its solidarity with the ordinary people who are leading this change with great courage.",
        "Apart from that, the organization has insisted that Gotabaya Rajapaksa should be held accountable not only for mismanagement of the economy, but also for the murder and disappearance of tens of thousands of Tamil people and many journalists in the period from 2005 to 2009, and for the disappearance of thousands of Sinhalese youth in 1989.",
        "'The country's emerging economic crisis has led to the coalescence of such a progressive political group, and that coalescence has achieved a most revolutionary success in a peaceful manner.",
        "This moment is the rebirth that Sri Lanka has achieved after independence', the British-based diaspora Tamil organization World Tamil Council said in its statement.",
        "The World Tamil Council has pointed out that Gotabaya Rajapaksa's departure from the country and his resignation from the presidency were the most important moves and no one expected such incidents to happen about 6 months ago.",
        "The diaspora Tamil organization has insisted that Gotabaya Rajapaksa should be held accountable not only for mismanagement of the economy but also for the murder and disappearance of tens of thousands of Tamil people and many journalists in the period from 2005 to 2009, and for the disappearance of thousands of Sinhalese youth in 1989.",
        "It has also been pointed out that until a stable, democratic, accountable and inclusive government is established by holding an interim all-party government with the participation of representatives who can respect the aspirations of the people involved in the struggle and then holding general elections to establish a government that can represent the people, it is necessary to continue such struggles towards change in a peaceful and constitutional manner.",
        "'The new government that can be established in the current situation is in a position to carry out some very challenging tasks. Especially in relation to debt restructuring, difficult negotiations with international countries and international public financing structures should be undertaken and urgent financial assistance should be requested for the purchase of essential items such as food, fuel, and medicine.",
        "Similarly, while the people have already suffered greatly as a result of the economic crisis, the World Tamil Council has stated that strong economic recovery measures should be taken so as not to affect them further."
      ],
